WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.860 align:middle line:90%


00:00:06.860 --> 00:00:09.310 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:00:09.310 --> 00:00:19.630 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.630 --> 00:00:23.110 align:middle line:84%
>> OK, when I started, I thought
maybe it would be a movie

00:00:23.110 --> 00:00:24.303 align:middle line:90%
or a website.

00:00:24.303 --> 00:00:26.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Why don't we start
even before all of that?

00:00:26.220 --> 00:00:28.720 align:middle line:90%
Start with why.

00:00:28.720 --> 00:00:30.410 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:00:30.410 --> 00:00:34.720 align:middle line:84%
I started the project because
I wanted more happiness

00:00:34.720 --> 00:00:38.620 align:middle line:84%
in my life and in
my kids' lives.

00:00:38.620 --> 00:00:44.115 align:middle line:84%
But I realized I didn't even
know how to talk about it.

00:00:44.115 --> 00:00:45.490 align:middle line:84%
Sitting around
the kitchen table,

00:00:45.490 --> 00:00:49.330 align:middle line:84%
my own daughter told
me "I'm stressed out.

00:00:49.330 --> 00:00:54.080 align:middle line:84%
I want to be happy,
and I don't know how."

00:00:54.080 --> 00:00:56.660 align:middle line:84%
That was the start
of my journey.

00:00:56.660 --> 00:01:00.630 align:middle line:84%
And what I discovered is
that happiness can be taught.

00:01:00.630 --> 00:01:08.994 align:middle line:90%


00:01:08.994 --> 00:01:11.454 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:01:11.454 --> 00:01:18.342 align:middle line:90%


00:01:18.342 --> 00:01:22.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Any questions or any
argument, or any criticism,

00:01:22.660 --> 00:01:23.862 align:middle line:90%
most welcome.

00:01:23.862 --> 00:01:25.945 align:middle line:84%
>> You're going to be
transformed in this process.

00:01:25.945 --> 00:01:27.653 align:middle line:84%
As much as you want
to help other people,

00:01:27.653 --> 00:01:30.822 align:middle line:84%
this process is going
to inform your lives.

00:01:30.822 --> 00:01:33.364 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the greatest decisions
you can make in your life is

00:01:33.364 --> 00:01:34.697 align:middle line:90%
what you're going to do with it.

00:01:34.697 --> 00:01:37.060 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:39.700 align:middle line:84%
>> For some, it's
easier than others.

00:01:39.700 --> 00:01:43.840 align:middle line:84%
In our society,
depression is on the rise.

00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:46.676 align:middle line:84%
And teens are
especially susceptible.

00:01:46.676 --> 00:02:01.750 align:middle line:90%


00:02:01.750 --> 00:02:03.770 align:middle line:90%
But there is hope.

00:02:03.770 --> 00:02:18.253 align:middle line:90%


00:02:18.253 --> 00:02:20.670 align:middle line:84%
When I started the project, I
had heard really good things

00:02:20.670 --> 00:02:22.680 align:middle line:84%
about this teacher
named Ward Mailliard

00:02:22.680 --> 00:02:26.430 align:middle line:84%
at a small private school up in
the mountains near Santa Cruz.

00:02:26.430 --> 00:02:30.230 align:middle line:84%
>> So Randy came to
sit in on a class.

00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:32.040 align:middle line:84%
And it was just a
normal day for us.

00:02:32.040 --> 00:02:35.460 align:middle line:84%
>> But what I saw coming from
the kids and the interaction

00:02:35.460 --> 00:02:38.970 align:middle line:84%
between him and his
students just blew me away.

00:02:38.970 --> 00:02:42.860 align:middle line:84%
The quality of creative
thought, of self reflection,

00:02:42.860 --> 00:02:46.140 align:middle line:84%
It was exactly what
I was looking for.

00:02:46.140 --> 00:02:50.280 align:middle line:84%
I connected Ward with some other
unique teachers I had heard of,

00:02:50.280 --> 00:02:52.290 align:middle line:84%
a young principal
in Nigeria named

00:02:52.290 --> 00:02:54.660 align:middle line:84%
Emmanuel and a
first-grade teacher

00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:59.430 align:middle line:84%
named Yeshi at a school for
Tibetan exiles living in India.

00:02:59.430 --> 00:03:02.040 align:middle line:84%
The kids started talking
with each other by email

00:03:02.040 --> 00:03:06.100 align:middle line:84%
and sending videos and really
getting to know one another.

00:03:06.100 --> 00:03:09.420 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, what if we
could put our heads together

00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:11.910 align:middle line:84%
to make something that
we could then share

00:03:11.910 --> 00:03:14.445 align:middle line:90%
with other kids, other schools?

00:03:14.445 --> 00:03:17.910 align:middle line:84%
And what if we could get
kids talking together

00:03:17.910 --> 00:03:21.160 align:middle line:84%
about real ways to have more
happiness in their lives?

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:24.810 align:middle line:84%
>> An individual requires an
opportunity or an experience

00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:26.590 align:middle line:90%
to understand their potential.

00:03:26.590 --> 00:03:30.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think this was an
experience for all of us.

00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:34.830 align:middle line:84%
>> We try to take advantage
of the human situation,

00:03:34.830 --> 00:03:38.250 align:middle line:84%
because we know that
everybody wants to be happy.

00:03:38.250 --> 00:03:40.140 align:middle line:90%
Everybody needs compassion.

00:03:40.140 --> 00:03:42.330 align:middle line:90%
Everybody wants to be loved.

00:03:42.330 --> 00:03:46.270 align:middle line:84%
Things that are very, very
fundamental to human beings,

00:03:46.270 --> 00:03:47.070 align:middle line:90%
inescapable.

00:03:47.070 --> 00:03:48.700 align:middle line:90%
We can't run away from them.

00:03:48.700 --> 00:03:54.140 align:middle line:90%


00:03:54.140 --> 00:03:56.390 align:middle line:84%
>> People have always
told me to be special,

00:03:56.390 --> 00:04:00.690 align:middle line:84%
and I find it weird that I
don't feel special at all.

00:04:00.690 --> 00:04:05.110 align:middle line:90%


00:04:05.110 --> 00:04:06.403 align:middle line:90%
More happiness.

00:04:06.403 --> 00:04:08.070 align:middle line:84%
>> I really don't
know where I was born,

00:04:08.070 --> 00:04:09.870 align:middle line:84%
but I was born in
India, for sure.

00:04:09.870 --> 00:04:14.995 align:middle line:84%
But I have no idea,
because I'm an orphan, so.

00:04:14.995 --> 00:04:17.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Ever since I was little,
I've moved around from school

00:04:17.370 --> 00:04:19.029 align:middle line:90%
to school.

00:04:19.029 --> 00:04:21.660 align:middle line:84%
I guess I don't really allow
myself to become attached

00:04:21.660 --> 00:04:24.420 align:middle line:84%
to any place or look at
it as the only place I'm

00:04:24.420 --> 00:04:28.530 align:middle line:84%
going to stay, because, I
mean, nothing is forever.

00:04:28.530 --> 00:04:30.510 align:middle line:90%
>> I'll be happy at some point.

00:04:30.510 --> 00:04:32.760 align:middle line:84%
>> I hope it'll have
an impact on me,

00:04:32.760 --> 00:04:35.880 align:middle line:84%
because everyone really
wants to be happier.

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:40.350 align:middle line:90%


00:04:40.350 --> 00:04:43.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Happiness can be elusive.

00:04:43.080 --> 00:04:46.175 align:middle line:84%
With an increase in depression
comes an increase in suicides.

00:04:46.175 --> 00:05:04.340 align:middle line:90%


00:05:04.340 --> 00:05:10.040 align:middle line:84%
>> It's really stressful,
trying to keep myself as myself.

00:05:10.040 --> 00:05:13.200 align:middle line:84%
I really don't know
what to do about it.

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:15.800 align:middle line:90%
I was six when my mom died.

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:21.110 align:middle line:84%
She came home from the
hospital with my little sister.

00:05:21.110 --> 00:05:25.220 align:middle line:84%
And I remember her complaining
about her back hurting

00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:27.030 align:middle line:90%
and her head hurting.

00:05:27.030 --> 00:05:29.270 align:middle line:84%
And then I came
home from school,

00:05:29.270 --> 00:05:30.920 align:middle line:84%
and the ambulances
were out front.

00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:33.480 align:middle line:90%


00:05:33.480 --> 00:05:39.470 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of a nice
story to think about,

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:42.950 align:middle line:84%
like the whole "you'll
see them again in heaven"

00:05:42.950 --> 00:05:48.510 align:middle line:84%
and stuff like that,
but I don't know.

00:05:48.510 --> 00:05:52.270 align:middle line:84%
>> My father has been in the
hospital for quite a while.

00:05:52.270 --> 00:05:55.470 align:middle line:84%
He had a seizure
in June, and he was

00:05:55.470 --> 00:05:58.140 align:middle line:84%
in the hospital for
pancreatitis and died from that.

00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.720 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately I have
no control over that,

00:06:00.720 --> 00:06:04.600 align:middle line:90%
but I have to deal with it.

00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:06.350 align:middle line:84%
>> I just didn't
want to be who I was.

00:06:06.350 --> 00:06:09.310 align:middle line:84%
And I definitely tried really
hard to be somebody else,

00:06:09.310 --> 00:06:11.540 align:middle line:90%
and it just didn't work for me.

00:06:11.540 --> 00:06:15.700 align:middle line:84%
And then my past started
haunting me like no--

00:06:15.700 --> 00:06:17.810 align:middle line:84%
And then I just didn't
know what else to do,

00:06:17.810 --> 00:06:19.975 align:middle line:90%
and I started cutting myself.

00:06:19.975 --> 00:06:21.750 align:middle line:84%
And I think I have
this personality,

00:06:21.750 --> 00:06:25.630 align:middle line:84%
that if I start something,
I get really addicted to it.

00:06:25.630 --> 00:06:29.050 align:middle line:84%
I would do 20 cuts
everywhere, each day.

00:06:29.050 --> 00:06:35.740 align:middle line:84%
And I think I took some
rat something, ant killing

00:06:35.740 --> 00:06:38.202 align:middle line:90%
poisoning thing, something.

00:06:38.202 --> 00:06:40.660 align:middle line:84%
And my social worker was like,
"Wow, you're not going home.

00:06:40.660 --> 00:06:42.118 align:middle line:84%
You're going to a
mental hospital."

00:06:42.118 --> 00:06:44.900 align:middle line:90%
And then I was like, "Wow."

00:06:44.900 --> 00:06:47.360 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm a child of
divorced parents,

00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:51.840 align:middle line:84%
and I recently decided
to live with my father.

00:06:51.840 --> 00:06:53.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you just took my box.

00:06:53.240 --> 00:06:55.680 align:middle line:90%
>> [INAUDIBLE].

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.110 align:middle line:90%
Watch me cry.

00:06:58.110 --> 00:07:00.380 align:middle line:84%
>> It's a really
hard thing for me,

00:07:00.380 --> 00:07:04.450 align:middle line:84%
being able to feel
vulnerable around my dad.

00:07:04.450 --> 00:07:11.750 align:middle line:84%
>> I never felt that he would be
able to accept me if I gave up,

00:07:11.750 --> 00:07:20.120 align:middle line:84%
and I want to be able to feel
that he'll always love me.

00:07:20.120 --> 00:07:24.890 align:middle line:84%
So, I mean, if this
can teach me anything,

00:07:24.890 --> 00:07:28.640 align:middle line:84%
hopefully it's to be able
to talk to my father.

00:07:28.640 --> 00:07:32.690 align:middle line:84%
>> So how do we
get some answers?

00:07:32.690 --> 00:07:35.250 align:middle line:84%
We wanted to bring some other
voices into the project,

00:07:35.250 --> 00:07:39.290 align:middle line:84%
so we were looking for people
that the kids connected with.

00:07:39.290 --> 00:07:43.550 align:middle line:84%
Luke had just written an
essay comparing the Jedi code

00:07:43.550 --> 00:07:45.930 align:middle line:84%
with the principles
of the Dalai Lama.

00:07:45.930 --> 00:07:49.490 align:middle line:84%
And we were really fortunate
to be able to sit down

00:07:49.490 --> 00:07:51.050 align:middle line:90%
with George Lucas.

00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:52.250 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, my god.

00:07:52.250 --> 00:07:54.500 align:middle line:90%
We're going to see George Lucas.

00:07:54.500 --> 00:07:56.300 align:middle line:84%
We're going to see one
of my idols, someone

00:07:56.300 --> 00:08:00.065 align:middle line:84%
that I watch on the
"Star Wars" VHS and beta.

00:08:00.065 --> 00:08:01.190 align:middle line:90%
Do you want the lightsaber?

00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:03.710 align:middle line:90%
Do you want me to?

00:08:03.710 --> 00:08:06.890 align:middle line:84%
This guy created some of
my favorite characters.

00:08:06.890 --> 00:08:08.840 align:middle line:90%
This guy created my imagination.

00:08:08.840 --> 00:08:11.240 align:middle line:84%
I was a kid who grew
up on "Star Wars."

00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:12.612 align:middle line:90%
>> I guess this is the hot seat.

00:08:12.612 --> 00:08:14.110 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:14.110 --> 00:08:15.702 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:08:15.702 --> 00:08:16.502 align:middle line:90%
>> Good.

00:08:16.502 --> 00:08:19.490 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:20.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey, George.

00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:21.500 align:middle line:90%
What's going on?

00:08:21.500 --> 00:08:23.750 align:middle line:90%
It's me, Luke.

00:08:23.750 --> 00:08:25.130 align:middle line:90%
Hi, I'm Luke.

00:08:25.130 --> 00:08:27.512 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:08:27.512 --> 00:08:29.272 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:29.272 --> 00:08:31.730 align:middle line:84%
I was just wondering, how did
you put your own spirituality

00:08:31.730 --> 00:08:32.610 align:middle line:90%
into your films?

00:08:32.610 --> 00:08:35.240 align:middle line:84%
And even, did you put
your own spirituality,

00:08:35.240 --> 00:08:39.530 align:middle line:84%
or is it just something
that came to you creatively?

00:08:39.530 --> 00:08:45.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, creatively, or
spiritually, or intellectually,

00:08:45.740 --> 00:08:49.520 align:middle line:84%
you are your work, which is,
it's very hard to separate

00:08:49.520 --> 00:08:53.850 align:middle line:84%
the artist from what he does,
no matter who it is or what

00:08:53.850 --> 00:08:54.650 align:middle line:90%
they're doing.

00:08:54.650 --> 00:08:58.370 align:middle line:84%
Because the creativity is so
interconnected with your inner

00:08:58.370 --> 00:09:01.410 align:middle line:84%
being that it reflects
you as a person.

00:09:01.410 --> 00:09:06.110 align:middle line:84%
So if you want to know a
person, a filmmaker, or any kind

00:09:06.110 --> 00:09:08.222 align:middle line:84%
of artist, really, but
especially a filmmaker,

00:09:08.222 --> 00:09:09.680 align:middle line:84%
you can understand
a lot about them

00:09:09.680 --> 00:09:11.888 align:middle line:84%
just by looking at their
work, and you can understand

00:09:11.888 --> 00:09:14.150 align:middle line:90%
what kind of a person they are.

00:09:14.150 --> 00:09:15.330 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, I'm Madeline.

00:09:15.330 --> 00:09:16.130 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi.

00:09:16.130 --> 00:09:18.505 align:middle line:84%
>> What do you think are the
things which most contribute

00:09:18.505 --> 00:09:19.520 align:middle line:90%
to long term happiness?

00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:23.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, happiness is the result
of a combination of pleasure

00:09:23.780 --> 00:09:25.130 align:middle line:90%
and joy.

00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:29.030 align:middle line:84%
Short term happiness, which
is pleasure, is self-centered.

00:09:29.030 --> 00:09:30.620 align:middle line:84%
It's all about
getting something.

00:09:30.620 --> 00:09:34.670 align:middle line:84%
And so by its very
nature, short termed.

00:09:34.670 --> 00:09:36.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's by its very
nature, it's additive.

00:09:36.830 --> 00:09:39.320 align:middle line:84%
Which means that if
you do something once,

00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:42.120 align:middle line:84%
say you buy a car, the first
car you buy is fantastic.

00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:43.790 align:middle line:90%
It's an amazing experience.

00:09:43.790 --> 00:09:45.080 align:middle line:90%
You get this thing.

00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:47.450 align:middle line:84%
The second time you buy a
car, it's not so amazing.

00:09:47.450 --> 00:09:49.610 align:middle line:84%
So you have to buy a
bigger, fancier car in order

00:09:49.610 --> 00:09:52.220 align:middle line:84%
to get the same experience as
when you bought your first car.

00:09:52.220 --> 00:09:55.730 align:middle line:84%
And it just keeps going down
until you have six yachts, 12

00:09:55.730 --> 00:09:58.190 align:middle line:90%
airplanes, and 50 cars.

00:09:58.190 --> 00:10:01.790 align:middle line:84%
And even then, that
experience with those

00:10:01.790 --> 00:10:04.250 align:middle line:84%
will not equal the first
experience you had,

00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:06.920 align:middle line:90%
but joy is different.

00:10:06.920 --> 00:10:09.410 align:middle line:84%
Joy really has to do with
taking care of other people

00:10:09.410 --> 00:10:12.500 align:middle line:84%
and doing things for others
rather than for yourself.

00:10:12.500 --> 00:10:15.680 align:middle line:84%
It's an interesting
reality of why

00:10:15.680 --> 00:10:17.960 align:middle line:84%
we're here, that one of
the greatest pleasures

00:10:17.960 --> 00:10:20.030 align:middle line:90%
is making kids.

00:10:20.030 --> 00:10:24.950 align:middle line:84%
One of the greatest joys, or the
greatest joy, is raising kids.

00:10:24.950 --> 00:10:29.360 align:middle line:90%
And kids-- kids, I say children.

00:10:29.360 --> 00:10:31.800 align:middle line:84%
But children teach
you compassion.

00:10:31.800 --> 00:10:32.750 align:middle line:90%
They come out.

00:10:32.750 --> 00:10:34.292 align:middle line:84%
They're half an hour
old, and they're

00:10:34.292 --> 00:10:36.890 align:middle line:90%
already wiser than you are.

00:10:36.890 --> 00:10:38.570 align:middle line:84%
And what they know
how to teach you

00:10:38.570 --> 00:10:42.710 align:middle line:84%
is how to have
unconditional love, how

00:10:42.710 --> 00:10:45.950 align:middle line:84%
to be completely absorbed
with another human being

00:10:45.950 --> 00:10:49.320 align:middle line:90%
and devoted to that human being.

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:53.010 align:middle line:84%
And the joy you get from
them, and if you say,

00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:54.510 align:middle line:84%
"Gee, if I treated
everybody the way

00:10:54.510 --> 00:10:57.540 align:middle line:84%
I treat my little
six week old baby,

00:10:57.540 --> 00:11:00.210 align:middle line:90%
then I would have a lot of joy."

00:11:00.210 --> 00:11:06.570 align:middle line:84%
And you don't have to babies to
do it, but that's the hard way.

00:11:06.570 --> 00:11:09.480 align:middle line:90%
The easy way is to have kids.

00:11:09.480 --> 00:11:14.610 align:middle line:84%
Because you don't have a
choice You have to love them,

00:11:14.610 --> 00:11:18.630 align:middle line:90%
because they're very cute.

00:11:18.630 --> 00:11:23.010 align:middle line:84%
Until they turn into teenagers,
and then this other miracle

00:11:23.010 --> 00:11:26.290 align:middle line:84%
happens, where when they're
ready to leave and say

00:11:26.290 --> 00:11:27.090 align:middle line:90%
"I'm out of here.

00:11:27.090 --> 00:11:29.130 align:middle line:84%
I want to be
independent," they get

00:11:29.130 --> 00:11:32.590 align:middle line:84%
all gawky, and pimply, and ugly,
and they're not cute anymore,

00:11:32.590 --> 00:11:36.060 align:middle line:84%
so the parents are just as
willing to say, "OK, go off,

00:11:36.060 --> 00:11:37.890 align:middle line:90%
have your life."

00:11:37.890 --> 00:11:40.020 align:middle line:90%
But that's a true miracle.

00:11:40.020 --> 00:11:41.537 align:middle line:90%
I hope that answered something.

00:11:41.537 --> 00:11:44.520 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:11:44.520 --> 00:11:47.400 align:middle line:84%
>> We wanted to get a
scientific take on happiness,

00:11:47.400 --> 00:11:50.970 align:middle line:84%
so Luke and Nina went to
Seattle to talk to Dr.

00:11:50.970 --> 00:11:53.880 align:middle line:84%
Richard Davidson, one
of the world's leading

00:11:53.880 --> 00:11:55.450 align:middle line:90%
neuroscientists.

00:11:55.450 --> 00:11:59.032 align:middle line:90%
>> And speed and Luke, 1, 2, 3.

00:11:59.032 --> 00:12:00.990 align:middle line:84%
>> What's your definition
of lasting happiness?

00:12:00.990 --> 00:12:03.720 align:middle line:90%
Or not definition, what's your--

00:12:03.720 --> 00:12:05.520 align:middle line:84%
what brings you
lasting happiness?

00:12:05.520 --> 00:12:11.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, what brings me lasting
happiness is to do the work

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:14.370 align:middle line:84%
I'm doing and have
it help others.

00:12:14.370 --> 00:12:17.460 align:middle line:84%
From very early on,
I had the conviction

00:12:17.460 --> 00:12:21.540 align:middle line:84%
that the mind is
something that is really

00:12:21.540 --> 00:12:24.480 align:middle line:84%
important to our well-being
and our happiness,

00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:29.970 align:middle line:84%
and that if we can all improve
our minds in certain ways,

00:12:29.970 --> 00:12:31.950 align:middle line:84%
our well-being would
improve, and the world

00:12:31.950 --> 00:12:34.000 align:middle line:90%
can really be a better place.

00:12:34.000 --> 00:12:39.420 align:middle line:84%
So I very quickly got involved
in neuroplasticity research.

00:12:39.420 --> 00:12:42.210 align:middle line:84%
Neuroplasticity
is a word that we

00:12:42.210 --> 00:12:44.850 align:middle line:84%
use to describe the
fact that the brain can

00:12:44.850 --> 00:12:49.350 align:middle line:84%
change in response to experience
and in response to training.

00:12:49.350 --> 00:12:52.260 align:middle line:90%
This is really a new discovery.

00:12:52.260 --> 00:12:56.160 align:middle line:84%
We even have learned that
we grow new brain cells.

00:12:56.160 --> 00:12:58.830 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the mechanisms
of neuroplasticity.

00:12:58.830 --> 00:13:00.750 align:middle line:84%
We once thought
that the brain was

00:13:00.750 --> 00:13:03.210 align:middle line:84%
different than any other
organ in the body, in that it

00:13:03.210 --> 00:13:05.400 align:middle line:90%
didn't grow new brain cells.

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:09.240 align:middle line:84%
But we now know that that's
just totally wrong, that we

00:13:09.240 --> 00:13:11.070 align:middle line:90%
do grow new brain cells.

00:13:11.070 --> 00:13:16.350 align:middle line:84%
An average adult grows about
5,000 new cells every day.

00:13:16.350 --> 00:13:20.670 align:middle line:84%
And that provides the
scientific underpinnings

00:13:20.670 --> 00:13:23.940 align:middle line:84%
for understanding
how training our mind

00:13:23.940 --> 00:13:26.377 align:middle line:84%
can actually produce
enduring changes.

00:13:26.377 --> 00:13:28.710 align:middle line:84%
>> If you could just pick us
all up and shake us and say

00:13:28.710 --> 00:13:30.835 align:middle line:84%
something to us to make us
happier and make us less

00:13:30.835 --> 00:13:32.500 align:middle line:90%
depressed, what would it be.

00:13:32.500 --> 00:13:37.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I would say that to
appreciate the fact that all

00:13:37.590 --> 00:13:43.080 align:middle line:84%
of us, and youth in particular,
are in a constant state of flux

00:13:43.080 --> 00:13:49.650 align:middle line:84%
and change, and that gives
you radical possibilities

00:13:49.650 --> 00:13:52.650 align:middle line:90%
for growth and development.

00:13:52.650 --> 00:13:57.600 align:middle line:84%
Kids often get stuck in
patterns of self identification,

00:13:57.600 --> 00:14:00.300 align:middle line:84%
where they're identifying
with a particular subgroup.

00:14:00.300 --> 00:14:03.940 align:middle line:84%
They have a clique of friends
that they're hanging out with.

00:14:03.940 --> 00:14:06.150 align:middle line:84%
They listen to a
certain kind of music.

00:14:06.150 --> 00:14:08.310 align:middle line:90%
That's their identity.

00:14:08.310 --> 00:14:10.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's very
difficult to see change

00:14:10.770 --> 00:14:12.460 align:middle line:90%
when you're in the middle of it.

00:14:12.460 --> 00:14:15.720 align:middle line:84%
So who you think you are
at this point in time

00:14:15.720 --> 00:14:20.210 align:middle line:84%
is not necessarily who you're
going to be in the next moment.

00:14:20.210 --> 00:14:22.850 align:middle line:84%
>> As a producer, I've done
some films with the Dalai Lama

00:14:22.850 --> 00:14:27.620 align:middle line:84%
Foundation, and I thought, why
not try to have the students

00:14:27.620 --> 00:14:30.830 align:middle line:84%
and their teachers discuss
happiness with the Dalai Lama

00:14:30.830 --> 00:14:32.120 align:middle line:90%
himself?

00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:36.050 align:middle line:84%
I think his message reaches
across all kinds of boundaries.

00:14:36.050 --> 00:14:40.000 align:middle line:84%
And that really gave us
a good place to start.

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:44.040 align:middle line:84%
We asked for the
interview, and he said yes.

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:46.560 align:middle line:84%
>> The product is
the journey here.

00:14:46.560 --> 00:14:50.790 align:middle line:84%
By us engaging and making a
commitment without any sense

00:14:50.790 --> 00:14:52.980 align:middle line:84%
that anything is going
to come back from it.

00:14:52.980 --> 00:14:54.900 align:middle line:84%
And my hope is to
go on the journey

00:14:54.900 --> 00:14:57.840 align:middle line:84%
and to see how we're
changed by the journey.

00:14:57.840 --> 00:15:00.386 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm looking forward to it.

00:15:00.386 --> 00:15:03.670 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:15:03.670 --> 00:15:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> The second group of kids we
were taking to visit the Dalai

00:15:06.380 --> 00:15:11.158 align:middle line:84%
Lama were Emmanuel's
students from Nigeria.

00:15:11.158 --> 00:15:13.578 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:15:13.578 --> 00:15:23.330 align:middle line:90%


00:15:23.330 --> 00:15:26.630 align:middle line:84%
>> The students here in Nigeria
on this project have been

00:15:26.630 --> 00:15:30.500 align:middle line:84%
making contributions about the
understanding of happiness,

00:15:30.500 --> 00:15:33.950 align:middle line:84%
what makes them happy and
what makes them not happy.

00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:38.420 align:middle line:84%
>> Happiness, in my own opinion,
can be defined as a state

00:15:38.420 --> 00:15:45.140 align:middle line:84%
of being glad or happy, or it's
an inner expression of a good

00:15:45.140 --> 00:15:45.940 align:middle line:90%
feeling.

00:15:45.940 --> 00:15:49.720 align:middle line:90%


00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:55.120 align:middle line:84%
>> Whenever I help someone and
I make them feel they are human,

00:15:55.120 --> 00:15:56.540 align:middle line:90%
it makes me happy.

00:15:56.540 --> 00:15:59.980 align:middle line:84%
And whenever I succeed
in whatever I'm doing,

00:15:59.980 --> 00:16:01.540 align:middle line:90%
it also makes me happy.

00:16:01.540 --> 00:16:05.180 align:middle line:84%
>> There's one thing that I
know I'm not really happy about.

00:16:05.180 --> 00:16:08.380 align:middle line:84%
Like here in Nigeria, we have
so many people suffering.

00:16:08.380 --> 00:16:11.320 align:middle line:84%
If they don't go to school,
to join up with armed robbery,

00:16:11.320 --> 00:16:12.970 align:middle line:90%
corruption, so many things.

00:16:12.970 --> 00:16:16.240 align:middle line:84%
Because there's nobody
to take care of them.

00:16:16.240 --> 00:16:20.340 align:middle line:84%
But I'm praying to God if
you can just make me great,

00:16:20.340 --> 00:16:24.964 align:middle line:84%
I'll try my best to meet
people's needs, too.

00:16:24.964 --> 00:16:25.764 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:16:25.764 --> 00:16:28.620 align:middle line:90%


00:16:28.620 --> 00:16:31.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Everybody in the
world, wherever you are,

00:16:31.010 --> 00:16:32.810 align:middle line:84%
we are talking
about universality,

00:16:32.810 --> 00:16:35.130 align:middle line:84%
whether you are in the
US, you are in Nigeria,

00:16:35.130 --> 00:16:37.890 align:middle line:84%
you are in Ghana, Jamaica,
and whether you are black,

00:16:37.890 --> 00:16:41.390 align:middle line:84%
or white, or green, or blue, no
matter the kind of human being

00:16:41.390 --> 00:16:45.410 align:middle line:84%
you are, we naturally
want to be happy.

00:16:45.410 --> 00:16:50.130 align:middle line:84%
>> What makes me happy is when I
see I performed well in school.

00:16:50.130 --> 00:16:52.700 align:middle line:84%
>> Some girls, they are
working on the street.

00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:54.930 align:middle line:84%
They don't have anybody
to pay their school fees,

00:16:54.930 --> 00:16:56.760 align:middle line:84%
but I'm happy that
me, I'm in school.

00:16:56.760 --> 00:17:00.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Just being with my friends
and then telling jokes

00:17:00.010 --> 00:17:00.810 align:middle line:90%
to others.

00:17:00.810 --> 00:17:03.452 align:middle line:84%
>> When there is singing,
I feel very happy.

00:17:03.452 --> 00:17:05.160 align:middle line:84%
>> When you look into
your life tomorrow,

00:17:05.160 --> 00:17:07.778 align:middle line:84%
what do you see exactly
that makes you so happy?

00:17:07.778 --> 00:17:08.609 align:middle line:90%
>> Doctor.

00:17:08.609 --> 00:17:11.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, you want to be a doctor?

00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:16.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Every human being is still
in the process of becoming.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:18.690 align:middle line:84%
There is no human
being who is Perfect

00:17:18.690 --> 00:17:23.880 align:middle line:84%
the problem is that our
pursuit of happiness

00:17:23.880 --> 00:17:27.359 align:middle line:84%
is actually based on what
we understand by happiness.

00:17:27.359 --> 00:17:32.040 align:middle line:84%
And most of the time, our
understanding is limited.

00:17:32.040 --> 00:17:36.540 align:middle line:84%
And because it is limited, we
search for happiness wrongly.

00:17:36.540 --> 00:17:40.920 align:middle line:84%
General happiness is
lasting, and unchangeable,

00:17:40.920 --> 00:17:43.690 align:middle line:90%
and originates from within us.

00:17:43.690 --> 00:17:48.570 align:middle line:84%
>> Patience,
compassion, empathy.

00:17:48.570 --> 00:17:53.280 align:middle line:84%
And without happiness,
you can't have patience,

00:17:53.280 --> 00:17:57.570 align:middle line:84%
because when you're not happy,
anybody that offends you,

00:17:57.570 --> 00:18:00.320 align:middle line:84%
you will definitely
offend that person back.

00:18:00.320 --> 00:18:03.030 align:middle line:84%
So without happiness,
you can't have patience.

00:18:03.030 --> 00:18:04.500 align:middle line:90%
>> Happiness is love.

00:18:04.500 --> 00:18:06.630 align:middle line:90%
Happiness is compassion.

00:18:06.630 --> 00:18:08.520 align:middle line:90%
And happiness is peace.

00:18:08.520 --> 00:18:11.130 align:middle line:84%
Because like just a
family, when there

00:18:11.130 --> 00:18:14.065 align:middle line:84%
is no happiness in the family,
there will not be peace.

00:18:14.065 --> 00:18:15.620 align:middle line:84%
They don't understand
each other,

00:18:15.620 --> 00:18:19.110 align:middle line:84%
and they don't have
compassion between themselves.

00:18:19.110 --> 00:18:22.590 align:middle line:84%
>> So when you want to be happy,
based on our own definition,

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:23.610 align:middle line:90%
you have to show love.

00:18:23.610 --> 00:18:27.060 align:middle line:84%
If you show
compassion, you are not

00:18:27.060 --> 00:18:29.490 align:middle line:84%
happy to see other
people suffer.

00:18:29.490 --> 00:18:31.810 align:middle line:84%
When you see people in
need, you help them.

00:18:31.810 --> 00:18:35.580 align:middle line:84%
And love is directed
towards fellow human beings.

00:18:35.580 --> 00:18:37.160 align:middle line:90%
Have you ever been sad?

00:18:37.160 --> 00:18:38.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:18:38.280 --> 00:18:39.970 align:middle line:90%
>> So what made you sad?

00:18:39.970 --> 00:18:41.040 align:middle line:90%
That is one.

00:18:41.040 --> 00:18:43.610 align:middle line:84%
And how did you feel
when you were sad?

00:18:43.610 --> 00:18:45.920 align:middle line:90%
>> The day I lost my dad.

00:18:45.920 --> 00:18:49.350 align:middle line:84%
I was very sad, and
I feel like joining

00:18:49.350 --> 00:18:51.450 align:middle line:90%
him, feel like killing myself.

00:18:51.450 --> 00:18:53.340 align:middle line:90%
>> We share the same experience.

00:18:53.340 --> 00:18:58.180 align:middle line:84%
In a way, the pain of losing
a dad is not just a dad.

00:18:58.180 --> 00:18:58.980 align:middle line:90%
Remember that.

00:18:58.980 --> 00:19:00.090 align:middle line:90%
We are all connected.

00:19:00.090 --> 00:19:03.780 align:middle line:84%
The death of any human
being affects us.

00:19:03.780 --> 00:19:06.120 align:middle line:84%
You remember the
poem by John Donne?

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:08.340 align:middle line:84%
He says "Everyone's
death diminishes me,

00:19:08.340 --> 00:19:09.570 align:middle line:90%
because no man is an island.

00:19:09.570 --> 00:19:10.653 align:middle line:90%
We are part of the whole."

00:19:10.653 --> 00:19:18.940 align:middle line:90%


00:19:18.940 --> 00:19:21.800 align:middle line:84%
>> The third group of students
participating were from

00:19:21.800 --> 00:19:25.550 align:middle line:84%
the Tibetan Children's Village,
located in the town where

00:19:25.550 --> 00:19:27.200 align:middle line:90%
the Dalai Lama now lives.

00:19:27.200 --> 00:19:37.950 align:middle line:90%


00:19:37.950 --> 00:19:39.380 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:19:39.380 --> 00:19:52.990 align:middle line:90%


00:19:52.990 --> 00:19:55.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Most of my students,
they're from Tibet.

00:19:55.210 --> 00:20:00.510 align:middle line:84%
But when I joined TCV, I
was not at all a Tibetan.

00:20:00.510 --> 00:20:03.240 align:middle line:84%
Right from childhood, I
stayed among the Indians.

00:20:03.240 --> 00:20:05.490 align:middle line:84%
I never had Tibetans
as my friends,

00:20:05.490 --> 00:20:08.490 align:middle line:84%
so I could not speak in
my language fluently.

00:20:08.490 --> 00:20:10.830 align:middle line:84%
Most of the time, I
conversed with my parents

00:20:10.830 --> 00:20:12.950 align:middle line:84%
in English, or
sometimes in Nepali.

00:20:12.950 --> 00:20:14.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Ask me some questions.

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:17.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you have any message
to the California students?

00:20:17.170 --> 00:20:19.810 align:middle line:84%
>> I just want to tell them to
stop visiting McDonald's quite

00:20:19.810 --> 00:20:20.610 align:middle line:90%
often.

00:20:20.610 --> 00:20:22.380 align:middle line:84%
Most of my students
say, "Ma'am, I

00:20:22.380 --> 00:20:26.670 align:middle line:84%
haven't met my parents for the
past 15 years or 20 years."

00:20:26.670 --> 00:20:28.800 align:middle line:84%
And first of all,
when I heard them

00:20:28.800 --> 00:20:31.710 align:middle line:84%
say that, I thought they were
exaggerating, because I was

00:20:31.710 --> 00:20:34.530 align:middle line:84%
thinking, how can they not meet
their parents for the past 15

00:20:34.530 --> 00:20:35.800 align:middle line:90%
years or 20 years?

00:20:35.800 --> 00:20:38.430 align:middle line:84%
But the closer I got
to the community,

00:20:38.430 --> 00:20:41.700 align:middle line:84%
the more I started knowing
about the hardships they undergo

00:20:41.700 --> 00:20:44.760 align:middle line:90%
when they come to India.

00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:46.410 align:middle line:90%
There are no legal permissions.

00:20:46.410 --> 00:20:47.850 align:middle line:90%
That's why the escape.

00:20:47.850 --> 00:20:51.450 align:middle line:84%
They've crossed such
dangerous places

00:20:51.450 --> 00:20:55.950 align:middle line:84%
that probably we in our wildest
dreams would never think of.

00:20:55.950 --> 00:20:56.820 align:middle line:90%
It's so funny.

00:20:56.820 --> 00:20:59.940 align:middle line:84%
Right now, they look so happy,
and when you watch them,

00:20:59.940 --> 00:21:01.800 align:middle line:84%
you can never imagine
that they've gone

00:21:01.800 --> 00:21:04.680 align:middle line:90%
through this in their life.

00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:07.800 align:middle line:84%
I cannot walk a mile,
and I think, "OK,

00:21:07.800 --> 00:21:09.570 align:middle line:90%
maybe I should hire a cab."

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:11.400 align:middle line:84%
But these boys and
these young girls

00:21:11.400 --> 00:21:14.760 align:middle line:90%
have walked for days and months.

00:21:14.760 --> 00:21:16.530 align:middle line:84%
It's not easy to
be in their shoes.

00:21:16.530 --> 00:21:24.020 align:middle line:90%


00:21:24.020 --> 00:21:26.450 align:middle line:84%
>> With the trip to India and
the interview with the Dalai

00:21:26.450 --> 00:21:29.690 align:middle line:84%
Lama getting closer, we wanted
to talk to someone who had

00:21:29.690 --> 00:21:31.070 align:middle line:90%
already met him.

00:21:31.070 --> 00:21:34.130 align:middle line:84%
So Nina and John
Murray flew to New York

00:21:34.130 --> 00:21:35.630 align:middle line:90%
to talk with Richard Gere.

00:21:35.630 --> 00:21:41.816 align:middle line:90%


00:21:41.816 --> 00:21:42.616 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, I'm John.

00:21:42.616 --> 00:21:43.115 align:middle line:90%
Nice to meet you.

00:21:43.115 --> 00:21:43.614 align:middle line:90%
>> Hi, John.

00:21:43.614 --> 00:21:44.414 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm Nina.

00:21:44.414 --> 00:21:45.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Nina, how are you?

00:21:45.900 --> 00:21:46.733 align:middle line:90%
>> Nice to meet you.

00:21:46.733 --> 00:21:48.000 align:middle line:90%
>> Tony, how are you?

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:52.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Tony, I know you exist, too.

00:21:52.170 --> 00:21:55.310 align:middle line:84%
The camera's actually
a human being.

00:21:55.310 --> 00:21:57.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So if I could ask
you a quick question.

00:21:57.060 --> 00:21:57.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, go ahead.

00:21:57.860 --> 00:22:01.470 align:middle line:84%
>> We're asking people what
their definition of happiness

00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:07.380 align:middle line:84%
is, in terms of what brings
you happiness in your life?

00:22:07.380 --> 00:22:08.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Now's my moment?

00:22:08.280 --> 00:22:10.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:10.720 --> 00:22:15.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, happiness, in
Buddhism, is a truism,

00:22:15.240 --> 00:22:17.880 align:middle line:84%
which is fundamental whether
you're a Buddhist or not,

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:21.430 align:middle line:84%
but it is that we all move
towards happiness and away from

00:22:21.430 --> 00:22:22.230 align:middle line:90%
suffering.

00:22:22.230 --> 00:22:22.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:22:22.990 --> 00:22:23.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Always.

00:22:23.790 --> 00:22:26.160 align:middle line:84%
And however we define
happiness, that's

00:22:26.160 --> 00:22:27.785 align:middle line:84%
what we're always
moving towards.

00:22:27.785 --> 00:22:30.860 align:middle line:84%
And however we define suffering,
we're moving away from that.

00:22:30.860 --> 00:22:33.000 align:middle line:90%
But we can understand everyone.

00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:35.070 align:middle line:84%
Our enemies, our
friends, everyone

00:22:35.070 --> 00:22:37.237 align:middle line:84%
by looking at their actions
from that point of view.

00:22:37.237 --> 00:22:39.695 align:middle line:84%
>> But what about when you're
unhappy and when you're faced

00:22:39.695 --> 00:22:42.180 align:middle line:84%
with these challenges or the
suffering that you're trying

00:22:42.180 --> 00:22:43.120 align:middle line:90%
to escape?

00:22:43.120 --> 00:22:45.540 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, the reason that I
got involved with Buddhism is,

00:22:45.540 --> 00:22:48.420 align:middle line:90%
I was so unhappy.

00:22:48.420 --> 00:22:51.660 align:middle line:84%
And I saw everyone around
me being incredibly unhappy.

00:22:51.660 --> 00:22:53.160 align:middle line:90%
I said, "What is this about?

00:22:53.160 --> 00:22:54.730 align:middle line:90%
Are we stuck with this?"

00:22:54.730 --> 00:22:56.350 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't want
to accept that,

00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:58.590 align:middle line:84%
so I started looking around
for systems that would

00:22:58.590 --> 00:23:00.890 align:middle line:90%
give alternate possibilities.

00:23:00.890 --> 00:23:04.480 align:middle line:84%
And Buddhism was the
one that touched me.

00:23:04.480 --> 00:23:08.250 align:middle line:84%
Someone like the Dalai Lama, who
you'll meet, has been tested,

00:23:08.250 --> 00:23:13.832 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the life of His
Holiness is so extraordinary.

00:23:13.832 --> 00:23:16.410 align:middle line:84%
The testing is going
on, emotional testing,

00:23:16.410 --> 00:23:19.040 align:middle line:84%
psychological testing, physical
testing, that is going on,

00:23:19.040 --> 00:23:20.820 align:middle line:90%
it goes on constantly.

00:23:20.820 --> 00:23:23.190 align:middle line:84%
>> What are these tests
that you're speaking of?

00:23:23.190 --> 00:23:25.095 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, physical tests
like His Holiness?

00:23:25.095 --> 00:23:25.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:23:25.530 --> 00:23:27.655 align:middle line:84%
>> His Holiness had everything
taken away from him.

00:23:27.655 --> 00:23:29.405 align:middle line:84%
As a small baby, his
family was taken away

00:23:29.405 --> 00:23:30.738 align:middle line:90%
and his country was taking away.

00:23:30.738 --> 00:23:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, I know his story, but
how are you testing yourself,

00:23:33.270 --> 00:23:35.047 align:middle line:84%
or how would we be
testing ourselves?

00:23:35.047 --> 00:23:36.630 align:middle line:84%
>> I don't know your
personal history,

00:23:36.630 --> 00:23:39.150 align:middle line:84%
but I'm sure you've had
some suffering in your life.

00:23:39.150 --> 00:23:39.950 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:23:39.950 --> 00:23:44.160 align:middle line:84%
>> Whether it's operatic, huge,
or it's small and private.

00:23:44.160 --> 00:23:46.190 align:middle line:84%
But these are
tests to all of us.

00:23:46.190 --> 00:23:48.540 align:middle line:84%
And these are deep
challenges for all of us,

00:23:48.540 --> 00:23:52.290 align:middle line:84%
that are impediments to
our hearts opening up,

00:23:52.290 --> 00:23:54.430 align:middle line:90%
to feeling empathic.

00:23:54.430 --> 00:23:58.620 align:middle line:84%
If you can take that one time
that you were really hungry

00:23:58.620 --> 00:24:02.630 align:middle line:84%
for whatever reason, and then
multiply that by a million,

00:24:02.630 --> 00:24:06.810 align:middle line:84%
and think about all
the starving people,

00:24:06.810 --> 00:24:09.750 align:middle line:84%
that one time that
someone, I don't know,

00:24:09.750 --> 00:24:12.870 align:middle line:84%
a girl grabbed your hair and
pulled it and knocked you

00:24:12.870 --> 00:24:15.420 align:middle line:84%
down or whatever,
and then imagine

00:24:15.420 --> 00:24:18.090 align:middle line:84%
the millions of people
who are tortured every day

00:24:18.090 --> 00:24:21.000 align:middle line:90%
and identify with them.

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:23.760 align:middle line:84%
And these are challenges
to the reality

00:24:23.760 --> 00:24:26.450 align:middle line:90%
of the world we live in.

00:24:26.450 --> 00:24:29.070 align:middle line:84%
And a challenge to
what we do about it.

00:24:29.070 --> 00:24:31.040 align:middle line:84%
You're going to be
transformed in this process.

00:24:31.040 --> 00:24:32.748 align:middle line:84%
As much as you want
to help other people,

00:24:32.748 --> 00:24:35.510 align:middle line:84%
this process is going
to inform your lives.

00:24:35.510 --> 00:25:33.500 align:middle line:90%


00:25:33.500 --> 00:25:36.740 align:middle line:84%
>> We arrived in Delhi, and the
first thing we did on the very

00:25:36.740 --> 00:25:40.460 align:middle line:84%
first day is, we went
out to Kingsway Camp.

00:25:40.460 --> 00:25:44.270 align:middle line:84%
And this is a place that was
established by Gandhi, where

00:25:44.270 --> 00:25:47.570 align:middle line:84%
Gandhi used to stay in the very
early days of the independence

00:25:47.570 --> 00:25:48.620 align:middle line:90%
movement.

00:25:48.620 --> 00:25:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And he created this
place for the Harijans.

00:25:52.010 --> 00:25:53.510 align:middle line:84%
And they're the
poorest of the poor.

00:25:53.510 --> 00:25:55.700 align:middle line:90%
They're the scavenger caste.

00:25:55.700 --> 00:25:59.310 align:middle line:84%
And these kids, what they had
to offer us was their prayers.

00:25:59.310 --> 00:26:02.003 align:middle line:84%
And they sang these
Sanskrit prayers.

00:26:02.003 --> 00:26:04.418 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:26:04.418 --> 00:26:20.390 align:middle line:90%


00:26:20.390 --> 00:26:22.430 align:middle line:84%
>> They were all just
so happy to see us,

00:26:22.430 --> 00:26:26.120 align:middle line:84%
and it reminded me of
me being one of them,

00:26:26.120 --> 00:26:28.790 align:middle line:84%
standing in a
straight line waiting,

00:26:28.790 --> 00:26:31.350 align:middle line:84%
when some other foreigner came
in, the big smile that came

00:26:31.350 --> 00:26:32.150 align:middle line:90%
on my face.

00:26:32.150 --> 00:26:33.080 align:middle line:90%
It used to be me.

00:26:33.080 --> 00:26:41.830 align:middle line:90%


00:26:41.830 --> 00:26:44.010 align:middle line:84%
>> We left Delhi
for the orphanage,

00:26:44.010 --> 00:26:48.160 align:middle line:84%
at the Sri Ram ashram, which is
Mount Madonna's sister school

00:26:48.160 --> 00:26:49.240 align:middle line:90%
in India.

00:26:49.240 --> 00:26:51.465 align:middle line:84%
Both were founded by
students of Baba Hari

00:26:51.465 --> 00:26:54.620 align:middle line:90%
Dass, who is a silent monk.

00:26:54.620 --> 00:26:57.950 align:middle line:84%
Actually, the kids
know him as Baba-ji.

00:26:57.950 --> 00:27:00.250 align:middle line:84%
For Prabha, this is
where she grew up.

00:27:00.250 --> 00:27:03.970 align:middle line:84%
So this was a
homecoming for her.

00:27:03.970 --> 00:27:07.060 align:middle line:90%
>> Baba-ji is my dad, kind of.

00:27:07.060 --> 00:27:07.900 align:middle line:90%
He is my dad.

00:27:07.900 --> 00:27:12.460 align:middle line:84%
So when Baba-ji was a kid,
he went to an orphanage,

00:27:12.460 --> 00:27:15.540 align:middle line:84%
and he saw that the kids
weren't treated right.

00:27:15.540 --> 00:27:19.450 align:middle line:84%
And he was very sad, so
he made a promise that he

00:27:19.450 --> 00:27:20.780 align:middle line:90%
would open an orphanage.

00:27:20.780 --> 00:27:25.000 align:middle line:90%
And I was the fourth kid.

00:27:25.000 --> 00:27:28.055 align:middle line:84%
When a new kid comes, we
don't say "Oh, my god.

00:27:28.055 --> 00:27:28.930 align:middle line:90%
There's another one."

00:27:28.930 --> 00:27:33.290 align:middle line:84%
We just take him right in, and
that just fills up more love.

00:27:33.290 --> 00:27:34.490 align:middle line:90%
There's more help.

00:27:34.490 --> 00:27:37.030 align:middle line:84%
Like if the kid needs
help, we're there.

00:27:37.030 --> 00:27:39.820 align:middle line:84%
We've never seen family,
so this is our family.

00:27:39.820 --> 00:27:41.610 align:middle line:84%
I have no other
definition of a family.

00:27:41.610 --> 00:27:46.340 align:middle line:90%


00:27:46.340 --> 00:27:49.550 align:middle line:84%
Just being here, I can feel
the love coming my way.

00:27:49.550 --> 00:28:20.250 align:middle line:90%


00:28:20.250 --> 00:28:22.710 align:middle line:84%
We went to Har Ki
Pauri and I bet

00:28:22.710 --> 00:28:24.480 align:middle line:84%
there were more than
2,000 people there.

00:28:24.480 --> 00:28:31.500 align:middle line:84%
And just for that 15 minutes,
that amount of people come.

00:28:31.500 --> 00:28:33.990 align:middle line:90%
And it is spiritual.

00:28:33.990 --> 00:28:38.820 align:middle line:84%
In India, every festival
is celebrated with family

00:28:38.820 --> 00:28:41.630 align:middle line:90%
and a whole community.

00:28:41.630 --> 00:28:44.875 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know, and that
brings you more close.

00:28:44.875 --> 00:28:48.160 align:middle line:90%


00:28:48.160 --> 00:28:51.960 align:middle line:84%
>> There is just like hundreds,
just like thousands of people

00:28:51.960 --> 00:28:53.100 align:middle line:90%
just chilling.

00:28:53.100 --> 00:28:54.450 align:middle line:84%
And it was just really
surprising to think

00:28:54.450 --> 00:28:55.750 align:middle line:90%
that they do this every night.

00:28:55.750 --> 00:29:52.000 align:middle line:90%


00:29:52.000 --> 00:29:53.560 align:middle line:84%
>> These people have
barely anything,

00:29:53.560 --> 00:29:56.690 align:middle line:84%
yet they are happier than most
people that have absolutely

00:29:56.690 --> 00:29:57.490 align:middle line:90%
everything.

00:29:57.490 --> 00:29:58.780 align:middle line:90%
To me, this is true happiness.

00:29:58.780 --> 00:30:00.700 align:middle line:90%
These kids have true happiness.

00:30:00.700 --> 00:30:03.500 align:middle line:84%
Running around, playing,
being who they are,

00:30:03.500 --> 00:30:05.460 align:middle line:90%
this is like paradise.

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:08.790 align:middle line:90%


00:30:08.790 --> 00:30:10.440 align:middle line:90%
>> I hated everybody before.

00:30:10.440 --> 00:30:12.230 align:middle line:90%
I hated life.

00:30:12.230 --> 00:30:15.510 align:middle line:84%
And I just hated the fact
that people would smile.

00:30:15.510 --> 00:30:16.950 align:middle line:90%
I just hated laughing.

00:30:16.950 --> 00:30:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And I would just sit in my
room, and I would never smile,

00:30:20.640 --> 00:30:22.170 align:middle line:90%
and I would hate people.

00:30:22.170 --> 00:30:24.480 align:middle line:84%
And I would just
want to kill them.

00:30:24.480 --> 00:30:28.800 align:middle line:84%
And just going step by
step, it took me two years

00:30:28.800 --> 00:30:33.720 align:middle line:84%
to be the person I am today,
always smiling or laughing.

00:30:33.720 --> 00:30:39.870 align:middle line:84%
So that changed me, to know that
every person deserves to laugh,

00:30:39.870 --> 00:30:41.650 align:middle line:90%
and it's OK to laugh.

00:30:41.650 --> 00:30:44.250 align:middle line:84%
And I think just to
forgive, that I've

00:30:44.250 --> 00:30:46.740 align:middle line:84%
forgiven people who hurt
me when I was a kid,

00:30:46.740 --> 00:30:50.166 align:middle line:90%
and that changed, so.

00:30:50.166 --> 00:30:54.450 align:middle line:90%


00:30:54.450 --> 00:30:57.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm just very happy
right now with the kids.

00:30:57.770 --> 00:31:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And the memory is going to
be me laughing with them 24

00:31:01.520 --> 00:31:04.790 align:middle line:84%
hours every single day
at the most stupidest

00:31:04.790 --> 00:31:11.090 align:middle line:84%
jokes you can ever think of,
and we were just so stupid.

00:31:11.090 --> 00:31:13.400 align:middle line:84%
And when you talk about
it now, you just laugh.

00:31:13.400 --> 00:31:30.890 align:middle line:90%


00:31:30.890 --> 00:31:34.850 align:middle line:84%
>> It may look messy, but
I know where everything is.

00:31:34.850 --> 00:31:36.260 align:middle line:90%
My strategy is this.

00:31:36.260 --> 00:31:39.530 align:middle line:84%
If you unpack and
everything's around your bags,

00:31:39.530 --> 00:31:41.738 align:middle line:84%
it's much easier than having
to dig through your bags

00:31:41.738 --> 00:31:42.988 align:middle line:90%
constantly for all your stuff.

00:31:42.988 --> 00:31:43.880 align:middle line:90%
>> He's got a point.

00:31:43.880 --> 00:31:46.700 align:middle line:84%
>> It's going to be cool to
meet the people from the other

00:31:46.700 --> 00:31:53.420 align:middle line:84%
places and actually have
time to hang out with them.

00:31:53.420 --> 00:31:55.868 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how much Essen's
going to make us work.

00:31:55.868 --> 00:31:57.410 align:middle line:84%
>> I really want to
go to Dharamsala,

00:31:57.410 --> 00:32:01.800 align:middle line:84%
not just for the Dalai Lama,
but that place is going to be

00:32:01.800 --> 00:32:02.600 align:middle line:90%
incredible.

00:32:02.600 --> 00:32:04.370 align:middle line:84%
The Himalayas, the
air, that's going

00:32:04.370 --> 00:32:08.360 align:middle line:90%
to be incredibly beautiful.

00:32:08.360 --> 00:32:10.310 align:middle line:90%
>> You just fold shirts.

00:32:10.310 --> 00:32:11.960 align:middle line:84%
>> I really do need
to know how to--

00:32:11.960 --> 00:32:13.293 align:middle line:90%
>> Face down.

00:32:13.293 --> 00:32:14.210 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a good fold.

00:32:14.210 --> 00:32:22.840 align:middle line:90%


00:32:22.840 --> 00:32:25.910 align:middle line:84%
>> Here is an experience
that I will only get once

00:32:25.910 --> 00:32:26.710 align:middle line:90%
in a lifetime.

00:32:26.710 --> 00:32:29.830 align:middle line:84%
Especially to be in a
room with the Dalai Lama,

00:32:29.830 --> 00:32:30.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm very stoked.

00:32:30.730 --> 00:32:44.940 align:middle line:90%


00:32:44.940 --> 00:32:46.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, my god.

00:32:46.410 --> 00:32:50.830 align:middle line:90%


00:32:50.830 --> 00:32:54.010 align:middle line:84%
>> We began to see, in
real life experience,

00:32:54.010 --> 00:32:56.530 align:middle line:84%
some of the answers
we'd been looking for.

00:32:56.530 --> 00:32:58.990 align:middle line:84%
What brings lasting
happiness shows up

00:32:58.990 --> 00:33:04.180 align:middle line:84%
as gratitude, forgiveness,
helping others, and community.

00:33:04.180 --> 00:33:06.820 align:middle line:90%
The proof was all around us.

00:33:06.820 --> 00:33:09.820 align:middle line:84%
The children we met
demonstrated that you

00:33:09.820 --> 00:33:14.080 align:middle line:84%
can be very happy when you
tap into your inner resources.

00:33:14.080 --> 00:33:25.440 align:middle line:90%


00:33:25.440 --> 00:33:28.730 align:middle line:84%
>> I, Yeshi Kando, on
behalf of TCV school,

00:33:28.730 --> 00:33:33.994 align:middle line:84%
welcome everybody to India
and particularly to TCV.

00:33:33.994 --> 00:33:36.474 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:33:36.474 --> 00:33:43.914 align:middle line:90%


00:33:43.914 --> 00:33:55.818 align:middle line:84%
Impossible as they seem, you've
got to fight for everything.

00:33:55.818 --> 00:34:25.110 align:middle line:90%


00:34:25.110 --> 00:34:28.590 align:middle line:84%
>> Imagine a world where we're
taught the practices that

00:34:28.590 --> 00:34:32.219 align:middle line:84%
develop happiness and
emotional intelligence just

00:34:32.219 --> 00:34:35.880 align:middle line:84%
as we're taught
algebra or writing.

00:34:35.880 --> 00:34:40.260 align:middle line:84%
It is possible, and it
can change the world.

00:34:40.260 --> 00:34:42.090 align:middle line:90%
[SINGING]

00:34:42.090 --> 00:34:45.110 align:middle line:90%


00:34:45.110 --> 00:34:48.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Emmanuel, Faith, and Mercy
had a couple of problems

00:34:48.670 --> 00:34:52.210 align:middle line:84%
leaving Nigeria, but we
finally caught up with them

00:34:52.210 --> 00:34:53.380 align:middle line:90%
in Dharamsala.

00:34:53.380 --> 00:34:56.880 align:middle line:90%


00:34:56.880 --> 00:35:00.180 align:middle line:84%
We've been working towards
this for the entire year,

00:35:00.180 --> 00:35:05.170 align:middle line:84%
and now we were meeting face
to face for the first time.

00:35:05.170 --> 00:35:09.540 align:middle line:84%
>> So today, we want to try a
little bit different process

00:35:09.540 --> 00:35:12.720 align:middle line:90%
than maybe you're used to, OK?

00:35:12.720 --> 00:35:14.305 align:middle line:90%
And try not to be shy.

00:35:14.305 --> 00:35:16.180 align:middle line:84%
--The others, and then
just make your groups.

00:35:16.180 --> 00:35:20.880 align:middle line:90%


00:35:20.880 --> 00:35:24.010 align:middle line:84%
>> People find me very
serious and not so talkative,

00:35:24.010 --> 00:35:26.820 align:middle line:84%
but my few friends, I'm
the very jokey type,

00:35:26.820 --> 00:35:29.160 align:middle line:84%
and I can go on
talking with them.

00:35:29.160 --> 00:35:31.540 align:middle line:84%
Actually, I am
more comfortable--

00:35:31.540 --> 00:35:35.490 align:middle line:84%
>> What is that you want to
know about America that you

00:35:35.490 --> 00:35:37.145 align:middle line:90%
don't know?

00:35:37.145 --> 00:35:38.630 align:middle line:90%
>> I've seen a lot of movies.

00:35:38.630 --> 00:35:41.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, movies don't really
show America, you know?

00:35:41.840 --> 00:35:44.190 align:middle line:90%
>> We were accepted with love.

00:35:44.190 --> 00:35:48.470 align:middle line:84%
They opened their hands,
their arms wide to accept us,

00:35:48.470 --> 00:35:50.810 align:middle line:90%
not segregating us from others.

00:35:50.810 --> 00:35:54.750 align:middle line:84%
It was like we are all
from the same place.

00:35:54.750 --> 00:35:58.333 align:middle line:84%
>> Nowadays we are trying
really hard to speak English

00:35:58.333 --> 00:35:59.370 align:middle line:90%
in our classes.

00:35:59.370 --> 00:36:02.496 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you guys have
pretty much perfect English.

00:36:02.496 --> 00:36:05.600 align:middle line:84%
>> Thanks to our
teachers and all the--

00:36:05.600 --> 00:36:10.060 align:middle line:84%
>> So do you read
books in English or?

